definitions.definition: A number by which another (the multiplicand ) is to be multiplied.
examples: In the expression 5 × 7, the "5" is a multiplier .
The score multiplier increases each time you complete a level of the video game.

definitions.definition: An adjective indicating the number of times something is to be multiplied.
A ratio used to estimate total economic effect for a variety of economic activities.
Any of several devices used to enhance a signal

subdefinitions.definition: a coil ; when Johann Schweigger in 1820 invented the electric coil, increasing the electro-magnetic field from a single wire, this invention was called a multiplier .
